Market Data Handler

Goals:
Overall: Use historical NASDAQ ITCH data to help simulate reviceing market data.
1) Get sample data.
-> Done : Using data from 30/01/2019 from https://emi.nasdaq.com/ITCH/Nasdaq%20ITCH/
2) Read and Send data.
    2.1) Reading. Use mmap and create a simple checker. Use message type to infer the length and check the timestamp to see if it should be sent.

    For the simulation I think I'll want the ability to control the speed of messages for debugging and maybe for visuals if I decide to implement a GUI. So only send a message if the timestamp is >= the simulation time.

    2.2) Sending. NASDAQ uses a version of UPD when sending data for create a UPD host to send the messages when a message is ready.

3) Recieve data. Make a client that is able to listen to UPD and revice the binary messages
4) Decode message.
5) Handle the stock messages for a single symbol.
6) Implement GUI to show messages and price / other things for single stock.
7) ?hanlde multiple (all?) stocks
8) Step 6 but for all stocks







LLM generated milestones
1 Small parser that reads file and emits messages to stdout.
2 Simple replay server (max-speed + real-time) sending over chosen transport.
3 Minimal consumer that receives raw messages and prints decoded events.
4 Single-symbol orderbook module that consumes events and validates state.
5 Add persistence (raw journal + decoded events).
6 Add simulated order gateway and test round-trip orders vs. reconstructed book.
7 Scale tests, inject faults/latency, and profile.
